Nest could make it more difficult for hackers to break into Nest cameras, for instance, by making the log-in process more cumbersome.
For instance, if a computer from the same Internet-protocol address attempted to log into 10 Nest accounts, the algorithm would block that address from logging into any more accounts.
According to at least one expert, though, Nest users are still exposed.
Instantly, Fordham said, he found thousands of Nest accounts that he could access.
Fordham said he is miffed that it is still so easy to log into Nest accounts.